{
  "stem": "7157.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Maybe it comes from that, from that scenario in Stanislawow.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] So we made plans to escape.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And my, my stepfather-- incidentally, we called him Wujek. 'Wujek' is the Polish name-- equivalent-- meaning for 'uncle.' So I could never call him Dad, because my father-- obviously he wasn't my father.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But we called him Wujek.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And even today, we still call him Wujek, which in Polish means 'uncle.' So anyway, at this point, of course, they were together, Wujek and my mother.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And he had a sister in Warsaw that was, that had married a Gentile.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And through a contact with her, he was able to get some papers-- some non-Jewish or gentile papers drawn up under a false name.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And so arrangements were made that on the outside, if we were able to get out, we at least had some papers that we could then use and possibly try to escape.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So the way we escaped was-- and I do remember this, myself-- that Lola and Miriam-- I told you that this lady Lola was, like, my mother's best friend, not a relative, but a friend.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "In fact, she just died in this country, about six months ago, at the age of 92.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Lola and Miriam worked with my mother on this shift.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So my mother took some things with her.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I was under Miriam's coat.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "This was evidently approaching winter, and it was cold.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And my brother was under Lola's coat.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So, as they walked out of the ghetto, we were both being hidden by their coats and by the masses of people, as we were leaving the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they took us to the place where they worked, this apartment.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
